<div class="allianceSection">
	 <h4 class="header">Characteristic Species</h4>
	<div class="text"> <i>Carpobrotus</i> <i>chilensis</i>, <i>Carpobrotus</i> <i>edulis</i>, <i>Mesembryanthemum</i> <i>crystallinum</i> or other ice plant taxa are dominant in the herbaceous layer. Emergent trees and shrubs may be present at low cover. </div>
</div>

        
	
<div class="allianceSection">
	 <h4 class="header">Vegetation Layers</h4>
	<div class="text">  Herbs < 50 cm; cover is intermittent to continuous. </div>
</div>

        
<div class="allianceSection">
	 <h4 class="header">Membership Rules</h4>
	<ul class="text">
		
		<li><i>Carpobrotus edulis, Mesembryanthemum crystallinum, </i>or other ice plant strongly dominant (> 80% relative cover) close to the coast (cf. Keeler-Wolf et al. 2003a, Evens and San 2005, HDR 2014b, Rodriguez et al. 2017, Verdone and Evens 2010).</li>
		
		<li><i>Carpobrotus</i> and/or <i>Mesembryanthemum</i> > 50% relative cover on bluffs, dunes, or disturbed lands (Buck-Diaz et al. 2021, Sikes et al. 2021).</li>
		
	</ul>
</div>

        
	
<div class="allianceSection">
	 <h4 class="header">Habitats</h4>
	<div class="text"> Bluffs, disturbed land, sand dunes of immediate coastline.  </div>
</div>

        
